{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/3-1. Addition and Subtraction/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"minjun.blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5828a22e-8af5-5b75-a19a-978b3eb412fe","excerpt":"contents: 0-1. CA Intro Addition & Subtraction Addition: just do the binary addition with given numbers  Subtraction: do the binary addition with the negation of the second operand Half adder 1-bit a…","html":"<p>contents: <a href=\"/0-1.%20CA%20Intro\" data-wiki-link=\"true\">0-1. CA Intro</a></p>\n<h2>Addition &#x26; Subtraction</h2>\n<p><strong>Addition</strong>: just do the binary addition with given numbers </br></p>\n<p><strong>Subtraction</strong>: do the binary addition with the negation of the second operand</p>\n<h3>Half adder</h3>\n<p>1-bit adder without carry-input</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Input: two one bit-data A, B</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Output: sum(S), carry(C)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Full adder</h3>\n<p>1-bit adder with carry-input</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Input: two one bit-data A, B, carry(C<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">_{in}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4617em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">in</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Output: sum(S), carry(C<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">_{out}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2806em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Circuit design for addition and subtraction</h2>\n<h3>N-bit parallel binary adder</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Initial carry input is 0</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The i-th adder waits for the carry until it is generated by the (i-1)-th adder</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class='gatsby-resp-image-figure' style='margin-bottom: 16px;'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-wrapper' style='position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; '>\n      <a class='gatsby-resp-image-link' href='/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/62aaf/01%201.jpg' style='display: block' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-background-image' style=\"padding-bottom: 31.76470588235294%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class='gatsby-resp-image-image' alt='01 1.jpg' title='' src='/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/a22ce/01%201.jpg' srcset='/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/0b705/01%201.jpg 170w,\n/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/31389/01%201.jpg 340w,\n/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/a22ce/01%201.jpg 680w,\n/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/29373/01%201.jpg 1020w,\n/static/d28d3ff26078b9da60e689ef5e016fae/62aaf/01%201.jpg 1280w' sizes='(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px' style='width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;' loading='lazy' decoding='async'>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class='gatsby-resp-image-figcaption'>01 1.jpg</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3>Adder with subtraction (in two's complement)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Subtract = 0 or 1 (if subtract == 1, B<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow></mrow><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4617em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is inverted)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Subtract is also added as the initial carry (if subtract ==1, 1 is added)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class='gatsby-resp-image-figure' style='margin-bottom: 16px;'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-wrapper' style='position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; '>\n      <a class='gatsby-resp-image-link' href='/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/62aaf/02%201.jpg' style='display: block' target='_blank' rel='noopener'>\n    <span class='gatsby-resp-image-background-image' style=\"padding-bottom: 44.11764705882353%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class='gatsby-resp-image-image' alt='02 1.jpg' title='' src='/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/a22ce/02%201.jpg' srcset='/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/0b705/02%201.jpg 170w,\n/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/31389/02%201.jpg 340w,\n/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/a22ce/02%201.jpg 680w,\n/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/29373/02%201.jpg 1020w,\n/static/4659ee7a87c9c659cac5a53b543f80ab/62aaf/02%201.jpg 1280w' sizes='(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px' style='width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;' loading='lazy' decoding='async'>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class='gatsby-resp-image-figcaption'>02 1.jpg</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2>Overflow</h2>\n<p>Overflow occurs when computation results are too large (out of range)</p>\n<h3>When does it occur?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Add two positives or negatives + the sign of result is different with sources</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Subtract a negative from a positive + the sign of result is 1</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Subtract a positive from a negative + the sign of result is 0</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to detect Overflow?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Use <code class=\"language-text\">add, addi, sub</code> instructions</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>They cause exceptions on overflow</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>    - A program jumps to predefined exception handler address</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>e.g., Fortran does not allow overflows. So MIPS Fortran compilers always use <code class=\"language-text\">add, addi, sub</code></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to ignore Overflow?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Use <code class=\"language-text\">addu, addui, subu</code> instructions (u means unsigned)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>They do not cause exceptions on overflow</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>e.g., C ignores overflows. So MIPS C compilers always use <code class=\"language-text\">addu, addui, subu</code></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Addition and Subtraction","date":"2024년 08월 13일 12:08","updated":"2024년 10월 20일 18:10","tags":["study","컴퓨터구조"],"series":null},"fields":{"slug":"/3-1. Addition and Subtraction/","readingTime":{"minutes":1.405}}},"seriesList":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"d3ec48ed-9d11-50ee-9b04-eafe9716e54f","fields":{"slug":"/nuxt-katex/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Nuxt content에 Mathtype 사용하기"}}},{"node":{"id":"bfc974be-489f-5e60-936c-a4b7c25346a4","fields":{"slug":"/ZeroPage_지금그때_2022/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"2022 ZeroPage 지금그때"}}},{"node":{"id":"f8f7470f-000c-592f-9791-14400e103d5a","fields":{"slug":"/readme/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"README"}}},{"node":{"id":"0df526dc-c987-5222-8b4d-2047a9ad339f","fields":{"slug":"/why-obsidian/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"기존 블로그 대신 Obsidian을 택한 이유"}}},{"node":{"id":"7cb33a77-2599-5c14-bac0-3e29f2c9db8c","fields":{"slug":"/0-1. CA Intro/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Computer Architecture Intro"}}},{"node":{"id":"6157f41a-d065-58ac-981a-873c63d5df39","fields":{"slug":"/0-2. CA Overview/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"CA Overview"}}},{"node":{"id":"f3396416-b746-5b19-8c4f-1a7ea8d0ddeb","fields":{"slug":"/1-1. Defining Performance/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Defining Performance"}}},{"node":{"id":"5977ca74-78d5-58bc-9dd5-6